					{}
				],
				"synopsis": {
					"type": 23,
					"value": "Jaheira's youngest daughter is practicing with a sword outside the front door (Though she now runs in when she sees her, so this likely occurs after she's already seen Jaheira) she's demanding, inquisitive and insistent in a way you would imagine a younger Jaheira might have been. This conversation prompts when Jaheira returns for the first time, and I was aiming at this proposing \"Baldurs Gate always need saving and so few are capabler\" to play into Jaheira's personal dilemma"
				}
			}
